-- models/intermediate/int_approved_returns.sql
-- Pick one approved return per item using earliest return_id
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        return_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_id ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_id,
    return_date,
    reason
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_returns.sql
-- Join order items with approved returns to identify returned items
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity,
        oi.unit_price,
        CASE
            WHEN r.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1
            ELSE 0
        END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_approved_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_categories.sql
-- Enrich items with category information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        i.item_id,
        i.order_id,
        i.product_id,
        i.quantity,
        i.unit_price,
        i.is_returned,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }} i
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = i.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/marts/fct_return_rate_by_category.sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        category_name,
        SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
        SUM(quantity * is_returned) AS total_items_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_categories') }}
    GROUP BY category_name
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    ROUND(
        CAST(total_items_returned AS DECIMAL(10, 4)) / CAST(total_items_sold AS DECIMAL(10, 4)),
        4
    ) AS return_rate
FROM source
ORDER BY return_rate DESC
